        public void start()
        Description copied from class: TileReader
        Instructs the TileReader that more than one tile may be consecutively requested.

        This merely serves as a hint to the reader; tiles may be requested regardless of whether start() had previously been invoked.

        Overrides:

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Description copied from class: TileReader
        Instructs the TileReader that the bulk requests indicated by start() will cease.

        This merely serves as a hint to the reader; tiles may continue to be requested even after stop() has been invoked.

        Overrides:
        stop in class TileReader

      • disposeImpl

        public void disposeImpl()
        Description copied from class: TileReader
        Implementation specific disposal. Implementations should always invoke super.disposeImpl().

        The default implementation marks TileReader.valid as false.

        This method will always be externally synchronized on this.readLock.

        Overrides:
        disposeImpl in class AbstractTilePyramidTileReader

      • cancel

        protected void cancel()
        Description copied from class: TileReader
        Implements asynchronous cancel. This method is invoked by the actively servicing TileReader.ReadRequest and should never be invoked externally.

        The default implementation returns immediately.

        cancel in class TileReader
